title: 127: Autonomy
itunes:author: Philosophy Talk Starters
itunes:summary:
More at http://philosophytalk.org/shows/autonomy.

Philosophers call a person autonomous if she is responsible not just for what she does but also for the principles and rules that guide her. But does this really make sense? Aren't we all just products of culture, education and genes? Join John and Ken as they investigate the nature of autonomy with John Christman from Penn State University.
